1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:36,648
(Ten years ago)

3
00:01:36,648 --> 00:01:39,008
Can anyone solve this problem?

4
00:01:39,568 --> 00:01:40,887
Qiao Hailun.

5
00:01:41,488 --> 00:01:42,727
Come and give it a try.

6
00:01:55,488 --> 00:01:56,807
Qiao Hailun did it correctly.

7
00:01:57,367 --> 00:01:57,807
Well done.

8
00:01:59,208 --> 00:01:59,848
Very clever.

9
00:02:00,408 --> 00:02:02,087
You should learn from Qiao Hailun.

10
00:02:02,607 --> 00:02:03,727
Don't waste your days.

11
00:02:04,967 --> 00:02:05,928
Focus on your study.

12
00:02:06,048 --> 00:02:07,048
You think she is smart?

13
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:08,927
A girl in my class is very mature.

14
00:02:09,207 --> 00:02:10,008
I think so too.

15
00:02:10,008 --> 00:02:10,647
I know her.

16
00:02:11,167 --> 00:02:12,408
She looks kind of proud.

17
00:02:12,688 --> 00:02:13,607
You shut up!

18
00:02:13,607 --> 00:02:14,688
We're not laughing at you.

19
00:02:19,647 --> 00:02:20,207
You're back.

20
00:02:21,607 --> 00:02:23,167
Did you get your math test score back?

21
00:02:24,207 --> 00:02:25,047
89.

22
00:02:26,368 --> 00:02:27,327
Why is it so low?

23
00:02:27,607 --> 00:02:28,927
What's the top score?

24
00:02:29,528 --> 00:02:30,327
89.

25
00:02:31,607 --> 00:02:33,887
So was the test very hard this time?

26
00:02:37,767 --> 00:02:38,327
Mom.

27
00:02:39,528 --> 00:02:41,088
I want to buy a new bra.

28
00:02:43,207 --> 00:02:44,647
What? You want another one already?

29
00:02:45,128 --> 00:02:46,368
Why do you need another one?

30
00:02:47,607 --> 00:02:49,047
Let me take a look.

31
00:02:49,727 --> 00:02:51,327
Mom, don't look.

32
00:02:51,848 --> 00:02:52,568
I'm your mother.

33
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:53,607
Don't be shy.

34
00:02:56,088 --> 00:02:57,368
It really is a bit tight.

35
00:02:58,207 --> 00:02:59,487
It's time to buy a new one.

36
00:03:00,327 --> 00:03:00,887
You are

37
00:03:00,887 --> 00:03:02,088
developing too quickly.

38
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:04,688
You know, bras are expensive.

39
00:03:06,047 --> 00:03:08,688
Mom, were you like this
when you were young?

40
00:03:09,088 --> 00:03:11,207
Me? I was nothing like you.

41
00:03:11,688 --> 00:03:12,927
When I was your age,

42
00:03:13,167 --> 00:03:13,968
I cut my hair short.

43
00:03:14,368 --> 00:03:16,207
Everyone thought I was a boy.

44
00:03:18,167 --> 00:03:18,808
How about this?

45
00:03:19,008 --> 00:03:19,927
I'll make you a bra.

46
00:03:20,607 --> 00:03:21,408
Time for dinner.

47
00:03:26,008 --> 00:03:28,288
I made it.

48
00:03:28,848 --> 00:03:29,887
(My name is Qiao Hailun.)

49
00:03:30,688 --> 00:03:33,128
(Ever since I started developing,)

50
00:03:33,408 --> 00:03:35,248
(I've often been watched differently.)

51
00:03:35,927 --> 00:03:37,128
(I didn't know what to do.)

52
00:03:38,288 --> 00:03:39,167
(So I asked my mom.)

53
00:03:40,047 --> 00:03:42,368
(She told me to focus on studying.)

54
00:03:42,887 --> 00:03:45,887
(As long as my grades were good,
I could ignore those stares.)

55
00:03:46,848 --> 00:03:48,128
(I believed her.)

56
00:03:48,887 --> 00:03:51,408
(I got into a prestigious university
as I hoped.)

57
00:03:52,647 --> 00:03:53,727
(A popular major.)

58
00:03:53,927 --> 00:03:55,047
(A bustling city.)

59
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,248
(A promising future.)

60
00:03:56,887 --> 00:03:59,767
(The world slowly unfolded before me.)

61
00:04:00,808 --> 00:04:02,128
(But unexpectedly,)

62
00:04:02,568 --> 00:04:05,128
(those stares never went away.)

63
00:04:08,128 --> 00:04:08,848
I heard

64
00:04:08,848 --> 00:04:11,808
that many kids start caring
about appearance after starting college.

65
00:04:11,887 --> 00:04:13,927
They hang out with classmates.

66
00:04:14,008 --> 00:04:15,288
Don't follow that example.

67
00:04:15,528 --> 00:04:16,327
I know.

68
00:04:16,568 --> 00:04:18,048
I never spend money carelessly.

69
00:04:18,488 --> 00:04:19,728
We aren't with you.

70
00:04:19,928 --> 00:04:21,008
You take care of yourself.

71
00:04:22,527 --> 00:04:24,008
Don't worry, Mom.

72
00:04:24,168 --> 00:04:25,688
I'm in college now.

73
00:04:26,008 --> 00:04:28,128
Now it's my turn to look after you.

74
00:04:33,704 --> 00:04:39,464
(Half Flame, Half Sea)

75
00:04:41,529 --> 00:04:46,696
=Episode 9=
(Surprise)

76
00:04:49,728 --> 00:04:50,527
What's happening?

77
00:04:52,407 --> 00:04:53,087
He is laid off.

78
00:05:01,248 --> 00:05:03,207
It's starting already?

79
00:05:45,488 --> 00:05:47,207
Never thought
Lin Sai would get laid off.

80
00:05:48,048 --> 00:05:49,647
Her performance has always been good.

81
00:05:50,048 --> 00:05:50,887
Didn't you say

82
00:05:50,887 --> 00:05:52,048
it's about the boss's choice

83
00:05:52,048 --> 00:05:53,527
instead of performance or ratings?

84
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:54,688
I was just speculating.

85
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,327
I never expected the boss
to dislike her.

86
00:05:57,688 --> 00:05:58,928
I'm speechless, honestly.

87
00:06:02,128 --> 00:06:02,568
What?

88
00:06:03,647 --> 00:06:04,608
I'm looking at my hand.

89
00:06:05,287 --> 00:06:06,488
See? It won't stop shaking.

90
00:06:06,928 --> 00:06:08,248
I can't make it stop.

91
00:06:12,128 --> 00:06:13,087
Anyone got heart pills?

92
00:06:13,568 --> 00:06:14,248
Give me one.

93
00:06:17,928 --> 00:06:18,168
Here.

94
00:06:19,368 --> 00:06:20,008
You have them?

95
00:06:25,008 --> 00:06:27,527
Hailun, you seem very calm.

96
00:06:29,568 --> 00:06:30,008
No.

97
00:06:30,488 --> 00:06:32,488
I have a report due
before quitting time.

98
00:06:33,808 --> 00:06:34,647
See now?

99
00:06:35,287 --> 00:06:36,887
She knows she's safe for today.

100
00:06:37,608 --> 00:06:38,207
Come on.

101
00:06:38,207 --> 00:06:39,488
That's not what I meant.

102
00:06:42,312 --> 00:06:44,287
(Tao Ling)

103
00:06:44,287 --> 00:06:45,928
(Are you sure I'm safe?)

104
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,384
(Yes.)

105
00:06:56,767 --> 00:06:58,408
(Then, who in our team
will be laid off?)

106
00:07:11,808 --> 00:07:14,368
(Did Li Dongming tell you
who's getting laid off from our team?)

107
00:07:24,488 --> 00:07:25,407
I don't know.

108
00:07:37,568 --> 00:07:38,327
Impossible.

109
00:07:39,887 --> 00:07:41,048
Impossible! Why?

110
00:07:43,808 --> 00:07:44,608
No way.

111
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:49,736
Hello?

112
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:57,488
Okay, I got it.

113
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:44,167
Sorry.

114
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:45,287
I'm sorry.

115
00:08:45,287 --> 00:08:46,368
It's okay.

116
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:13,527
Qiao Hailun.

117
00:09:13,968 --> 00:09:14,527
It was you.

118
00:09:14,608 --> 00:09:15,887
You took my spot, didn't you?

119
00:09:16,287 --> 00:09:18,128
You were the one
who should have been laid off.

120
00:09:19,728 --> 00:09:21,848
Tao Ling, stop talking nonsense.

121
00:09:22,248 --> 00:09:24,008
What does your layoff have to do
with me?

122
00:09:24,008 --> 00:09:24,887
Really?

123
00:09:25,128 --> 00:09:27,248
You have the lowest overall score!

124
00:09:27,248 --> 00:09:28,368
Yet they fired me!

125
00:09:28,368 --> 00:09:29,368
That's because of you!

126
00:09:30,047 --> 00:09:31,608
How can you be so shameless?

127
00:09:31,608 --> 00:09:33,488
Do you think
no one knows you sleep your way

128
00:09:33,488 --> 00:09:34,527
to the top?

129
00:09:38,488 --> 00:09:39,368
Stop spreading rumors!

130
00:09:39,368 --> 00:09:40,128
Spreading rumors?

131
00:09:40,128 --> 00:09:41,728
Others might not know you, but I do!

132
00:09:42,128 --> 00:09:44,488
The company should
release everyone's evaluation scores!

133
00:09:44,687 --> 00:09:46,527
I don't believe
my score is lower than yours.

134
00:09:46,968 --> 00:09:48,887
Tao Ling,
you're too emotional right now.

135
00:09:49,368 --> 00:09:51,208
Let's talk elsewhere.

136
00:09:51,448 --> 00:09:52,088
How?

137
00:09:52,167 --> 00:09:52,968
Where can we talk?

138
00:09:53,368 --> 00:09:55,272
She's slept with Li Dongming
on business trips!

139
00:09:55,488 --> 00:09:57,167
You should be the one fired, not me!

140
00:09:57,488 --> 00:09:58,728
That's slander!

141
00:09:59,248 --> 00:10:00,887
My performance is better than yours!

142
00:10:01,248 --> 00:10:02,807
Your scores are the lowest!

143
00:10:02,848 --> 00:10:03,807
What about yours?

144
00:10:03,927 --> 00:10:04,687
Why fire me?

145
00:10:04,927 --> 00:10:05,647
I won't accept it!

146
00:10:05,848 --> 00:10:06,927
I'm not leaving.

147
00:10:07,088 --> 00:10:07,968
I refuse to accept it!

148
00:10:08,407 --> 00:10:09,088
Why?

149
00:10:09,167 --> 00:10:10,047
Why should I be fired?

150
00:10:10,368 --> 00:10:11,488
Don't explain!

151
00:10:11,767 --> 00:10:12,968
I've been here for many years.

152
00:10:13,567 --> 00:10:14,887
- Qu Bo, stop it!
- I won't accept this!

153
00:10:14,887 --> 00:10:15,728
- Let go of me!
- Calm down.

154
00:10:15,728 --> 00:10:16,287
Stop shouting!

155
00:10:16,287 --> 00:10:17,328
I won't accept it!

156
00:10:17,328 --> 00:10:18,488
Who is better than me?

157
00:10:18,848 --> 00:10:19,567
- Let go!
- Get out!

158
00:10:19,807 --> 00:10:20,927
- Why fire me?
- Get out.

159
00:10:21,088 --> 00:10:22,248
Let me see the Chairman!

160
00:10:22,248 --> 00:10:23,887
I'll complain to headquarters about you!

161
00:10:23,887 --> 00:10:24,368
Shut up.

162
00:10:34,608 --> 00:10:36,407
Mr. Liu, thank you for this matter.

163
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:38,527
Well,

164
00:10:39,488 --> 00:10:40,488
my dad asked me

165
00:10:41,088 --> 00:10:42,527
to invite you over for dinner

166
00:10:42,687 --> 00:10:43,887
when you're free.

167
00:10:45,167 --> 00:10:46,687
Alright, I'll wait for your news.

168
00:10:48,887 --> 00:10:50,008
Didn't we have a deal?

169
00:10:50,008 --> 00:10:51,448
Why did you fire Tao?

170
00:10:51,807 --> 00:10:52,767
Don't worry.

171
00:10:53,887 --> 00:10:55,647
I found her a position at Keruina.

172
00:10:56,008 --> 00:10:57,448
Her salary will be raised by 30%.

173
00:10:58,407 --> 00:10:59,927
Chen from Keruina owes me a favor.

174
00:11:00,807 --> 00:11:03,527
Everyone in our team knows
Tao's performance was the worst.

175
00:11:03,767 --> 00:11:05,167
If I hadn't fired her,

176
00:11:05,167 --> 00:11:06,488
others would have complained.

177
00:11:06,608 --> 00:11:07,567
Yes, that makes sense.

178
00:11:09,167 --> 00:11:10,248
Why didn't you tell me?

179
00:11:10,807 --> 00:11:12,767
Who knows if she can act well enough?

180
00:11:13,047 --> 00:11:14,968
What if when HR told her

181
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:15,887
she was fired,

182
00:11:16,047 --> 00:11:17,167
she actually laughed?

183
00:11:18,807 --> 00:11:19,448
You know what?

184
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:21,248
That's possible.

185
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:25,687
But what if

186
00:11:25,728 --> 00:11:26,647
she exposes me?

187
00:11:27,248 --> 00:11:28,887
It's not like you were never exposed.

188
00:11:29,088 --> 00:11:30,208
But now, you're doing fine.

189
00:11:30,488 --> 00:11:31,088
Alright,

190
00:11:31,248 --> 00:11:32,128
fine.

191
00:11:34,128 --> 00:11:35,047
I know what to do.

192
00:11:38,248 --> 00:11:38,807
Thanks.

193
00:11:53,927 --> 00:11:54,527
Cao Lei.

194
00:11:55,088 --> 00:11:56,488
Get Qiao Hailun,

195
00:11:56,887 --> 00:11:58,047
and come with me to Beijing.

196
00:12:04,608 --> 00:12:05,368
Feeling better?

197
00:12:08,208 --> 00:12:08,927
Much better.

198
00:12:09,527 --> 00:12:10,848
I'm just a bit worried.

199
00:12:13,968 --> 00:12:14,767
Tao Ling...

200
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,567
Tao Ling's layoff has nothing
to do with you.

201
00:12:17,248 --> 00:12:18,128
She came in last.

202
00:12:18,128 --> 00:12:19,287
Everyone knows it.

203
00:12:19,608 --> 00:12:20,448
Nobody can help her.

204
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:25,167
Cao Lei.

205
00:12:25,887 --> 00:12:26,887
What's your idea of this?

206
00:12:27,767 --> 00:12:28,687
I have no idea.

207
00:12:29,488 --> 00:12:30,647
Although we got along well

208
00:12:30,968 --> 00:12:31,807
as colleagues,

209
00:12:32,608 --> 00:12:33,647
I believe this is normal.

210
00:12:34,887 --> 00:12:36,407
From middle school to high school,

211
00:12:36,608 --> 00:12:37,448
and to university,

212
00:12:38,128 --> 00:12:39,047
bachelor's degree

213
00:12:39,848 --> 00:12:40,647
to master's degree,

214
00:12:41,088 --> 00:12:42,567
actually, most people around us

215
00:12:42,647 --> 00:12:43,767
have been eliminated.

216
00:12:44,328 --> 00:12:45,448
Besides, layoffs are normal.

217
00:12:46,248 --> 00:12:47,687
People's fortunes shift.

218
00:12:48,128 --> 00:12:51,328
She might thrive elsewhere.

219
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:53,728
Listen to what Cao Lei said.

220
00:12:54,208 --> 00:12:55,128
Learn from him.

221
00:13:02,407 --> 00:13:04,287
I love Cocoon so much.

222
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:05,608
I went there once.

223
00:13:05,968 --> 00:13:06,807
I miss it.

224
00:13:08,248 --> 00:13:08,887
Cocoon?

225
00:13:09,287 --> 00:13:10,328
What an interesting name.

226
00:13:10,527 --> 00:13:11,488
Any special meaning?

227
00:13:11,647 --> 00:13:13,488
I heard it comes from an idiom.

228
00:13:13,608 --> 00:13:15,112
Breaking the cocoon into a butterfly.

229
00:13:17,368 --> 00:13:18,527
Come have fun.

230
00:13:18,968 --> 00:13:20,488
Why not come today?

231
00:13:20,968 --> 00:13:22,488
How about tonight? I'll arrange it.

232
00:13:23,848 --> 00:13:24,887
I can't do it today.

233
00:13:25,287 --> 00:13:27,008
I'm heading to the airport soon.

234
00:13:28,128 --> 00:13:28,887
Maybe another time.

235
00:13:29,527 --> 00:13:30,927
Okay, no problem.

236
00:13:31,527 --> 00:13:32,488
Sorry, Barry.

237
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:34,208
I forgot to tell you something.

238
00:13:35,608 --> 00:13:36,167
You go ahead.

239
00:13:37,128 --> 00:13:38,208
Let me walk you out.

240
00:13:38,208 --> 00:13:39,767
Okay. Bye.

241
00:13:42,488 --> 00:13:44,088
Barry mentioned Cocoon several times.

242
00:13:44,527 --> 00:13:46,128
Seems he genuinely likes it.

243
00:13:52,208 --> 00:13:53,008
Not really.

244
00:13:54,088 --> 00:13:56,448
He hasn't come once since it opened.

245
00:14:04,328 --> 00:14:04,728
So?

246
00:14:06,728 --> 00:14:07,488
I heard something.

247
00:14:08,088 --> 00:14:10,488
Dong Yue is dating
Shen Mo's only daughter.

248
00:14:11,448 --> 00:14:12,047
I see.

249
00:14:12,488 --> 00:14:13,448
Dong Yue is something.

250
00:14:13,887 --> 00:14:17,128
He has secured our biggest distributor.

251
00:14:17,968 --> 00:14:18,608
In the future,

252
00:14:18,608 --> 00:14:20,208
if Shen Mo backs him,

253
00:14:20,887 --> 00:14:23,927
the Sales Director position
will definitely be Dong Yue's.

254
00:14:24,407 --> 00:14:25,167
No.

255
00:14:26,248 --> 00:14:28,208
Shen Mo is our biggest distributor.

256
00:14:28,647 --> 00:14:30,968
Peter, the Sales VP,

257
00:14:31,647 --> 00:14:33,527
is clearly bought by Shen Mo already.

258
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:35,728
If our Sales Director

259
00:14:36,128 --> 00:14:37,287
becomes Shen Mo's son-in-law,

260
00:14:38,167 --> 00:14:41,008
I might as well hand GST to Shen Mo.

261
00:14:44,287 --> 00:14:46,128
I heard
Barry strongly supports Zhao Mei.

262
00:14:46,887 --> 00:14:47,728
Are you planning

263
00:14:48,088 --> 00:14:50,448
to appoint a woman as Sales Director?

264
00:14:50,887 --> 00:14:53,527
I don't think
Barry genuinely wants Zhao Mei.

265
00:14:54,088 --> 00:14:55,167
He's playing power games.

266
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:58,008
Xu Yuntian used to have unilateral say
over the sales.

267
00:14:58,248 --> 00:15:00,687
Now, he lets Dong Yue,
Tang Lide, and Zhao Mei compete

268
00:15:00,887 --> 00:15:02,807
against each other.

269
00:15:03,088 --> 00:15:05,647
It creates tensions,
promoting sales growth.

270
00:15:06,887 --> 00:15:07,488
Tension.

271
00:15:08,008 --> 00:15:08,687
I like it too.

272
00:15:09,608 --> 00:15:11,767
But I prefer looking for tension,

273
00:15:11,887 --> 00:15:13,287
not letting it come to me.

274
00:15:13,848 --> 00:15:16,608
Let's find a way to push things along.

275
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:21,088
Or invite Barry for another meal

276
00:15:21,887 --> 00:15:23,088
and see what he really wants.

277
00:15:28,287 --> 00:15:30,167
Dong Yue, what are your thoughts?

278
00:15:31,687 --> 00:15:32,208
Well,

279
00:15:32,208 --> 00:15:34,328
Barry hasn't shown me clear favoritism.

280
00:15:34,608 --> 00:15:35,208
Ultimately,

281
00:15:35,687 --> 00:15:36,887
he doesn't know me well

282
00:15:37,608 --> 00:15:38,248
or trust me.

283
00:15:39,368 --> 00:15:41,608
This trust isn't just based
on professional skills.

284
00:15:42,248 --> 00:15:44,047
He's different from you.
You own the company.

285
00:15:44,728 --> 00:15:46,088
To put it bluntly,

286
00:15:46,088 --> 00:15:48,328
he's just a high-level employee.

287
00:15:49,488 --> 00:15:50,248
In his mind,

288
00:15:50,728 --> 00:15:52,848
personal gain comes
before company interests.

289
00:15:53,128 --> 00:15:55,407
So he wants the new Sales Director

290
00:15:56,088 --> 00:15:57,488
not only to be professional

291
00:15:57,848 --> 00:15:59,927
but also loyal to him personally.

292
00:16:01,167 --> 00:16:02,407
I think Dong Yue is right.

293
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:04,248
That's how Barry acts.

294
00:16:04,527 --> 00:16:06,848
He had an issue with Xu Yuntian before

295
00:16:06,848 --> 00:16:08,248
because Xu Yuntian disobeyed him.

296
00:16:10,368 --> 00:16:11,328
What should we do?

297
00:16:11,968 --> 00:16:13,248
I want to meet him in private.

298
00:16:14,328 --> 00:16:15,407
He will go to Shanghai.

299
00:16:15,608 --> 00:16:16,248
I'll fly there.

300
00:16:17,128 --> 00:16:18,248
Meeting in Shanghai

301
00:16:18,248 --> 00:16:20,608
is definitely better
than meeting in Guangzhou.

302
00:16:22,488 --> 00:16:24,008
Will he meet you privately?

303
00:16:25,128 --> 00:16:25,992
I'll think of a way.

304
00:16:28,887 --> 00:16:29,687
Good evening.

305
00:16:41,887 --> 00:16:42,448
Shen Xing?

306
00:16:48,647 --> 00:16:49,647
You caught me.

307
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,287
How many times have I told you?

308
00:16:55,287 --> 00:16:56,208
You can touch anything

309
00:16:56,208 --> 00:16:56,927
but this guitar.

310
00:16:57,647 --> 00:16:59,047
Then play it for me!

311
00:17:04,087 --> 00:17:05,047
I've forgotten how.

312
00:17:05,688 --> 00:17:07,127
You just don't want to play for me.

313
00:17:08,367 --> 00:17:08,888
Are you mad?

314
00:17:10,408 --> 00:17:10,728
No.

315
00:17:11,607 --> 00:17:13,168
Liar. I already know.

316
00:17:13,408 --> 00:17:15,287
I didn't know
your mom sent the rice cake,

317
00:17:15,287 --> 00:17:16,767
or I wouldn't have thrown it away.

318
00:17:22,287 --> 00:17:22,767
Hold on.

319
00:17:27,008 --> 00:17:27,464
What's up?

320
00:17:28,008 --> 00:17:29,168
Didn't you call me?

321
00:17:31,527 --> 00:17:32,607
Yes, I wanted to tell you

322
00:17:32,607 --> 00:17:34,408
that Zeng Zixuan came
to me for an interview.

323
00:17:35,087 --> 00:17:35,888
She approached you?

324
00:17:36,127 --> 00:17:36,807
I was surprised.

325
00:17:36,888 --> 00:17:37,527
She said

326
00:17:37,527 --> 00:17:39,567
she wanted to learn more about sales.

327
00:17:40,008 --> 00:17:42,127
Maybe she'll be the next Liang Danning.

328
00:17:43,248 --> 00:17:44,567
Thanks for letting me know.

329
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:47,448
There's a cockroach!

330
00:17:52,008 --> 00:17:53,168
Looks like you're busy.

331
00:17:53,488 --> 00:17:54,408
I'm hanging up.

332
00:17:55,008 --> 00:17:55,367
Bye.

333
00:18:05,648 --> 00:18:07,488
Barry just said
he'd be in Shanghai tomorrow.

334
00:18:07,728 --> 00:18:10,168
I'm flying straight
from Beijing to Shanghai tomorrow.

335
00:18:11,008 --> 00:18:12,287
I'll try to convince him

336
00:18:12,728 --> 00:18:13,448
that he

337
00:18:13,728 --> 00:18:15,688
has no other candidate

338
00:18:15,888 --> 00:18:17,287
for the Sales Director position.

339
00:18:17,488 --> 00:18:18,408
He can only choose you.

340
00:18:22,648 --> 00:18:23,527
Thanks.

341
00:18:24,008 --> 00:18:26,087
Have a safe trip then.

342
00:18:26,527 --> 00:18:27,968
Take care.

343
00:18:29,367 --> 00:18:29,888
So,

344
00:18:29,888 --> 00:18:32,527
I'll go back a day later.
I'll be back the day after tomorrow.

345
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:43,968
I'm going to Shanghai tomorrow.

346
00:18:43,968 --> 00:18:45,567
You two don't need to go with me.

347
00:18:47,688 --> 00:18:49,367
I'm meeting Barry.

348
00:18:50,767 --> 00:18:51,728
You come with me.

349
00:18:52,168 --> 00:18:52,527
Okay.

350
00:18:54,847 --> 00:18:55,807
What's wrong?

351
00:18:56,208 --> 00:18:57,327
Why the long faces?

352
00:18:59,728 --> 00:19:00,807
I left for just a minute.

353
00:19:00,807 --> 00:19:01,567
What happened?

354
00:19:05,168 --> 00:19:06,287
There's a message

355
00:19:07,408 --> 00:19:09,168
saying Qu Bo took sleeping pills.

356
00:19:09,607 --> 00:19:10,567
Qu Bo?

357
00:19:13,607 --> 00:19:15,408
The cheerful young guy?

358
00:19:15,888 --> 00:19:16,807
How could this happen?

359
00:19:17,008 --> 00:19:17,567
Is it serious?

360
00:19:17,728 --> 00:19:18,928
He's in the hospital now.

361
00:19:19,648 --> 00:19:21,127
We don't know if he'll be okay.

362
00:19:21,567 --> 00:19:22,968
Probably not serious.

363
00:19:27,527 --> 00:19:28,567
How did this happen?

364
00:19:31,527 --> 00:19:32,847
It's just a layoff. Well...

365
00:19:42,488 --> 00:19:44,327
I have another appointment.
I have to go.

366
00:20:07,311 --> 00:20:11,502
(Flight Ticket to Shanghai)

367
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:16,367
Mom.

368
00:20:17,127 --> 00:20:18,448
Have you been taking the Q10?

369
00:20:21,087 --> 00:20:21,607
Yes,

370
00:20:22,248 --> 00:20:23,847
the health supplement for the heart.

371
00:20:24,327 --> 00:20:25,168
Remember to take it.

372
00:20:26,287 --> 00:20:27,127
Remind Dad

373
00:20:27,287 --> 00:20:28,127
to take it as well.

374
00:20:29,607 --> 00:20:30,448
It isn't expensive.

375
00:20:33,208 --> 00:20:34,208
Don't worry.

376
00:20:34,888 --> 00:20:37,648
By the way,
I bought you and Dad clothes.

377
00:20:38,127 --> 00:20:39,367
Remember to check your texts.

378
00:20:39,448 --> 00:20:40,888
I'll send you a pickup code.

379
00:20:44,888 --> 00:20:46,448
I earn a good salary.

380
00:20:46,807 --> 00:20:47,807
My boss values me highly.

381
00:20:49,928 --> 00:20:50,648
Don't worry.

382
00:20:51,807 --> 00:20:52,767
Don't worry about me.

383
00:20:53,448 --> 00:20:56,287
Alright, go watch TV. Bye.

384
00:20:59,448 --> 00:21:00,578
Hello.

385
00:21:03,368 --> 00:21:04,527
24 yuan.

386
00:21:04,688 --> 00:21:05,416
Put it together.

387
00:21:05,567 --> 00:21:06,008
Got it.

388
00:21:06,248 --> 00:21:06,648
No need.

389
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:07,168
No.

390
00:21:08,168 --> 00:21:10,047
45 yuan in total. I'll scan you.

391
00:21:10,047 --> 00:21:10,327
Thanks.

392
00:21:10,367 --> 00:21:10,767
Thank you.

393
00:21:12,287 --> 00:21:13,127
Let me heat it up.

394
00:21:15,567 --> 00:21:18,688
Qu Bo's situation upsets me
just as much as it does you.

395
00:21:21,327 --> 00:21:22,567
Senior Partners

396
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:23,928
just had a conference call.

397
00:21:24,928 --> 00:21:26,688
The company will try to help him.

398
00:21:28,488 --> 00:21:30,047
I also sent some money to his parents

399
00:21:30,047 --> 00:21:30,928
to show my concern.

400
00:21:34,952 --> 00:21:39,692
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

401
00:21:44,142 --> 00:21:46,062
♪Too much of shame♪

402
00:21:46,408 --> 00:21:49,204
♪To waste it crying♪

403
00:21:51,662 --> 00:21:53,582
♪Leave all behind you♪

404
00:21:53,582 --> 00:21:55,862
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

405
00:21:55,982 --> 00:21:58,211
♪You know how far you've gone♪

406
00:21:58,346 --> 00:22:00,622
♪In the fire you rise again♪

407
00:22:01,767 --> 00:22:03,728
That was already the seventh round
of interviews.

408
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:05,800
Over 100 candidates were waiting.

409
00:22:05,888 --> 00:22:07,488
I arrived at Ruijin at 9 AM.

410
00:22:07,847 --> 00:22:09,544
I didn't get interviewed until 10:30 PM.

411
00:22:09,847 --> 00:22:10,607
Waited that long.

412
00:22:10,607 --> 00:22:12,008
Yeah, I didn't eat all day.

413
00:22:12,168 --> 00:22:14,127
I feared they might need me,
so I didn't leave.

414
00:22:14,527 --> 00:22:15,688
I asked them a few times.

415
00:22:15,688 --> 00:22:17,888
They told me to be patient
and wait a little longer.

416
00:22:17,888 --> 00:22:20,367
So I just waited in the lounge.

417
00:22:20,767 --> 00:22:22,488
I waited until past ten.

418
00:22:23,047 --> 00:22:24,767
I thought to myself,
what a crappy company.

419
00:22:24,968 --> 00:22:25,888
I'm quitting.

420
00:22:25,888 --> 00:22:26,767
So I started to go.

421
00:22:27,607 --> 00:22:29,847
Just then,
I ran into the CEO at the time.

422
00:22:30,168 --> 00:22:32,287
I'd seen his picture on the website.

423
00:22:32,567 --> 00:22:33,367
So I recognized him.

424
00:22:33,768 --> 00:22:35,432
I said, "Are you going to interview me?"

425
00:22:36,607 --> 00:22:39,047
He said, "What's wrong, young man?
Haven't done yet?"

426
00:22:39,248 --> 00:22:39,807
I said, "Yes."

427
00:22:40,648 --> 00:22:41,767
He called the interviewer.

428
00:22:42,087 --> 00:22:43,488
He shouted, "What's going on?"

429
00:22:43,488 --> 00:22:44,688
"He hasn't worked here yet."

430
00:22:44,688 --> 00:22:46,567
"You can't make him work
overtime already."

431
00:22:59,127 --> 00:23:00,287
Thanks for comforting me.

432
00:23:02,888 --> 00:23:03,888
Feeling better?

433
00:23:10,952 --> 00:23:15,692
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

434
00:23:20,142 --> 00:23:22,062
♪Too much of shame♪

435
00:23:22,408 --> 00:23:25,204
♪To waste it crying♪

436
00:23:27,662 --> 00:23:29,582
♪Leave all behind you♪

437
00:23:29,582 --> 00:23:31,862
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

438
00:23:31,982 --> 00:23:34,211
♪You know how far you've gone♪

439
00:23:34,346 --> 00:23:36,622
♪In the fire you rise again♪

440
00:23:36,808 --> 00:23:39,168
♪You made it through the worst♪

441
00:23:39,367 --> 00:23:40,248
Put it together.

442
00:23:41,087 --> 00:23:41,688
Mr. Li.

443
00:23:42,367 --> 00:23:43,488
Let me pay.

444
00:23:43,888 --> 00:23:45,127
3,890 in total.

445
00:23:45,408 --> 00:23:47,248
Spread your legs a bit wider.

446
00:23:47,527 --> 00:23:48,367
Yes, a little wider.

447
00:23:48,408 --> 00:23:51,607
A male boss took a female employee
to play golf.

448
00:23:52,408 --> 00:23:53,968
You tell me you don't understand?

449
00:23:55,168 --> 00:23:56,448
Stick your butt out a little.

450
00:23:56,448 --> 00:23:57,287
Yes, like this.

451
00:23:57,320 --> 00:23:59,851
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

452
00:23:59,931 --> 00:24:02,153
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

453
00:24:02,295 --> 00:24:03,376
♪But I don't want to♪

454
00:24:05,448 --> 00:24:07,367
You're so supportive of Mr. Li.

455
00:24:08,462 --> 00:24:09,847
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

456
00:24:09,847 --> 00:24:11,968
Tell me. Do you like Mr. Li?

457
00:24:12,127 --> 00:24:15,327
Just use one evaluation score

458
00:24:15,327 --> 00:24:17,168
to decide an employee's fate?

459
00:24:17,168 --> 00:24:18,767
That's too arbitrary and unscientific.

460
00:24:22,367 --> 00:24:24,888
Li Dongming likes taking you
to social events so much

461
00:24:24,888 --> 00:24:26,847
because you have big boobs.

462
00:24:32,488 --> 00:24:33,924
♪Leave all behind you♪

463
00:24:34,028 --> 00:24:36,515
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

464
00:24:36,698 --> 00:24:38,827
♪You know how far you've gone♪

465
00:24:39,014 --> 00:24:41,354
♪In the fire you rise again♪

466
00:24:41,422 --> 00:24:43,688
♪You made it through the worst♪

467
00:24:44,048 --> 00:24:46,126
♪The best is yet to come♪

468
00:24:46,375 --> 00:24:48,545
♪The best is yet to come♪

469
00:24:51,246 --> 00:24:52,398
♪Isn't it magical♪

470
00:24:52,398 --> 00:24:56,044
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

471
00:24:56,078 --> 00:24:57,934
♪And I see them sparkling♪

472
00:24:58,158 --> 00:25:00,289
♪Nobody knows♪

473
00:25:00,910 --> 00:25:02,984
♪What tomorrow brings♪

474
00:25:03,208 --> 00:25:05,531
♪You made it through the worst♪

475
00:25:05,718 --> 00:25:07,926
♪The best is yet to come♪

476
00:25:08,213 --> 00:25:10,362
♪The best is yet to come♪

477
00:25:10,658 --> 00:25:12,072
♪Isn't it magical♪

478
00:25:12,072 --> 00:25:14,284
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

479
00:25:14,358 --> 00:25:16,712
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

480
00:25:16,712 --> 00:25:17,800
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

481
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:21,251
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

482
00:25:21,704 --> 00:25:23,978
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

483
00:25:24,392 --> 00:25:25,256
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

484
00:25:25,256 --> 00:25:26,776
♪Isn't it magical♪

485
00:25:31,968 --> 00:25:33,728
- Long time no see.
- Long time no see.

486
00:25:34,527 --> 00:25:35,367
Come on in.

487
00:25:38,488 --> 00:25:39,047
For you.

488
00:25:39,847 --> 00:25:40,567
For me?

489
00:25:41,648 --> 00:25:42,968
Thanks.

490
00:25:45,087 --> 00:25:45,728
Another guest?

491
00:25:46,807 --> 00:25:48,584
Also from Guangzhou.
From a consulting firm.

492
00:25:48,688 --> 00:25:49,168
Okay.

493
00:25:49,367 --> 00:25:50,168
Barry.

494
00:25:50,527 --> 00:25:51,567
Dong Yue's here.

495
00:25:54,287 --> 00:25:54,807
Hi, Barry.

496
00:25:54,807 --> 00:25:55,488
Dong Yue.

497
00:25:55,807 --> 00:25:56,208
Hi.

498
00:25:58,287 --> 00:25:59,208
How have you been?

499
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:00,047
Pretty good.

500
00:26:00,168 --> 00:26:00,728
Good.

501
00:26:00,728 --> 00:26:02,008
Look, my new Fender.

502
00:26:02,367 --> 00:26:04,408
Fender? Sounds like a bag.

503
00:26:04,688 --> 00:26:05,367
Don't be silly.

504
00:26:05,367 --> 00:26:06,047
Take a seat.

505
00:26:07,448 --> 00:26:08,008
Thank you.

506
00:26:13,767 --> 00:26:14,448
Have some wine?

507
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:15,047
Sure.

508
00:26:15,047 --> 00:26:16,287
Gennadiy or Moonlight City?

509
00:26:17,208 --> 00:26:18,168
I'll have Ming Jue.

510
00:26:18,448 --> 00:26:20,248
You actually like Ming Jue whiskey too?

511
00:26:20,767 --> 00:26:22,527
Yes, this whiskey has a unique flavor.

512
00:26:22,648 --> 00:26:23,408
You like it too?

513
00:26:23,607 --> 00:26:24,527
Yes.

514
00:26:25,008 --> 00:26:26,648
Some people think it tastes fishy.

515
00:26:27,607 --> 00:26:28,527
But I find it fragrant.

516
00:26:29,287 --> 00:26:30,047
To be honest,

517
00:26:30,248 --> 00:26:31,488
out of all GST's liquors,

518
00:26:32,047 --> 00:26:33,248
this is my favorite.

519
00:26:35,008 --> 00:26:36,728
Lisa doesn't even know,

520
00:26:37,767 --> 00:26:39,728
or I would think she told you.

521
00:26:41,047 --> 00:26:41,607
Barry.

522
00:26:42,367 --> 00:26:43,367
It's Pink Floyd.

523
00:26:43,888 --> 00:26:45,127
Pink Floyd.

524
00:26:46,208 --> 00:26:47,488
Dong Yue, thank you.

525
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:50,448
Thanks.

526
00:26:51,488 --> 00:26:52,527
Dong Yue came all the way.

527
00:26:52,527 --> 00:26:53,847
You must have a serious talk.

528
00:26:54,127 --> 00:26:55,208
I'm very busy today.

529
00:26:55,208 --> 00:26:55,888
I won't join you.

530
00:27:02,408 --> 00:27:03,168
I have an idea.

531
00:27:03,928 --> 00:27:05,888
But I can't bring it up
at the sales meeting.

532
00:27:07,327 --> 00:27:07,968
Go ahead.

533
00:27:09,367 --> 00:27:11,464
I analyzed the sales data
from the past five years.

534
00:27:11,928 --> 00:27:15,287
I found that although we still
hold the largest market share,

535
00:27:15,367 --> 00:27:17,567
we've actually hit a bottleneck.

536
00:27:17,607 --> 00:27:18,448
It's not just us.

537
00:27:19,127 --> 00:27:20,008
Wilson is the same.

538
00:27:20,648 --> 00:27:22,087
The main reason for this bottleneck

539
00:27:22,087 --> 00:27:24,248
is that our distributors
have hit their bottleneck.

540
00:27:25,928 --> 00:27:27,624
It's the era of e-commerce direct sales.

541
00:27:27,968 --> 00:27:29,488
Every brand wants

542
00:27:29,928 --> 00:27:32,928
to sell products directly
from the production line to consumers.

543
00:27:33,648 --> 00:27:35,168
Yet in our industry,

544
00:27:35,767 --> 00:27:38,448
we still follow the old sales model.

545
00:27:38,847 --> 00:27:42,127
I believe the best way
to break through bottlenecks

546
00:27:42,607 --> 00:27:44,408
is to break free
from distributor constraints.

547
00:27:44,872 --> 00:27:46,152
Deal directly with consumers.

548
00:27:48,928 --> 00:27:51,208
I heard
you're dating Shen Mo's daughter.

549
00:27:53,287 --> 00:27:54,024
That's irrelevant.

550
00:27:55,008 --> 00:27:55,767
Professionally,

551
00:27:56,287 --> 00:27:57,087
I am a salesman.

552
00:27:57,408 --> 00:27:58,208
He's a distributor.

553
00:27:59,208 --> 00:28:01,127
And you are my boss.

554
00:28:03,527 --> 00:28:05,607
Alright, let's have tea.

555
00:28:09,607 --> 00:28:10,248
See you, Barry.

556
00:28:11,127 --> 00:28:11,648
Bye, Lisa.

557
00:28:11,648 --> 00:28:12,008
Bye.

558
00:28:20,807 --> 00:28:22,127
He came to pledge loyalty to you?

559
00:28:24,287 --> 00:28:25,488
Dong Yue is quite clever.

560
00:28:26,287 --> 00:28:30,208
Of course. Otherwise,
how would he gain Shen Mo's favor?

561
00:28:32,168 --> 00:28:34,968
But you don't seem to like him much?

562
00:28:36,287 --> 00:28:37,127
That's not accurate.

563
00:28:37,567 --> 00:28:39,087
You clearly prefer Li Dongming.

564
00:28:40,767 --> 00:28:41,607
How do you know?

565
00:28:42,488 --> 00:28:45,047
Because you talked
outside intentionally.

566
00:28:46,928 --> 00:28:47,847
I can only say

567
00:28:48,527 --> 00:28:50,087
Dong Yue knows what I want.

568
00:28:50,807 --> 00:28:52,767
But Li Dongming knows what I fear.

569
00:28:53,087 --> 00:28:53,807
Go ahead.

570
00:28:54,928 --> 00:28:57,367
(A few hours ago)
You came to my home to talk to me.

571
00:28:57,968 --> 00:28:59,287
What is it?

572
00:28:59,928 --> 00:29:01,488
I did some preliminary research.

573
00:29:01,888 --> 00:29:05,168
Among GST China's director-level
and above executives,

574
00:29:05,168 --> 00:29:06,087
there are 12 in total.

575
00:29:06,527 --> 00:29:07,807
Only one is female.

576
00:29:07,807 --> 00:29:10,888
Women occupy less than 20 percent
of director positions.

577
00:29:11,208 --> 00:29:13,728
And they're all in non-core departments.

578
00:29:15,688 --> 00:29:16,888
Continue.

579
00:29:17,327 --> 00:29:21,168
But according to GST's global data,

580
00:29:21,688 --> 00:29:23,807
for executives
at the director level and above,

581
00:29:24,087 --> 00:29:26,607
women account for 31 percent.

582
00:29:26,767 --> 00:29:28,567
In the headquarters,

583
00:29:28,688 --> 00:29:30,327
it reaches 42 percent.

584
00:29:30,607 --> 00:29:31,976
Two years ago, it was 29 percent.

585
00:29:32,807 --> 00:29:39,047
So nearly all executives promoted
at HQ recently were women.

586
00:29:43,327 --> 00:29:46,968
Seems your team employs many women.

587
00:29:47,807 --> 00:29:49,968
Consulting firms
naturally have more female staff.

588
00:29:52,607 --> 00:29:53,127
Barry.

589
00:29:53,728 --> 00:29:54,767
I work for you.

590
00:29:55,367 --> 00:29:58,928
I want you to work
in China division more than anyone.

591
00:29:59,888 --> 00:30:01,087
To gain HQ's approval,

592
00:30:01,607 --> 00:30:04,648
you must align
with them in every aspect.

593
00:30:08,648 --> 00:30:10,127
So you're convinced

594
00:30:10,607 --> 00:30:11,607
by him?

595
00:30:11,607 --> 00:30:12,567
You'll promote his wife?

596
00:30:14,607 --> 00:30:15,607
I haven't decided yet.

597
00:30:16,127 --> 00:30:17,527
Li Dongming made valid points.

598
00:30:18,208 --> 00:30:19,488
But based on his logic,

599
00:30:19,488 --> 00:30:22,928
Zhao Mei becomes the only candidate
for Sales Director.

600
00:30:23,527 --> 00:30:25,847
But having a woman lead sales?

601
00:30:27,448 --> 00:30:28,208
I don't know.

602
00:30:29,128 --> 00:30:30,087
Anyway, I dislike him.

603
00:30:31,607 --> 00:30:33,408
Qiao Hailun is clearly his mistress.

604
00:30:34,008 --> 00:30:36,367
He brought his mistress to persuade you

605
00:30:36,367 --> 00:30:37,488
to promote his wife?

606
00:30:37,567 --> 00:30:39,127
Isn't this utterly bizarre?

607
00:30:39,488 --> 00:30:41,527
Is this some new form
of split personality?

608
00:30:43,008 --> 00:30:43,968
You're mistaken.

609
00:30:44,567 --> 00:30:45,807
It's not new.

610
00:30:46,087 --> 00:30:47,367
It's traditional.

611
00:30:49,047 --> 00:30:51,648
That's why I appreciate Li Dongming.

612
00:30:52,527 --> 00:30:53,527
He doesn't hide things.

613
00:30:57,607 --> 00:31:00,807
Will you follow this tradition?

614
00:31:00,928 --> 00:31:01,928
I couldn't do it.

615
00:31:03,847 --> 00:31:04,847
Following traditions

616
00:31:06,688 --> 00:31:07,607
is difficult.

617
00:31:10,127 --> 00:31:11,968
Peter, I just left Barry's home.

618
00:31:13,127 --> 00:31:14,087
But before I arrived,

619
00:31:14,087 --> 00:31:16,127
he likely met
with consulting firm people.

620
00:31:16,367 --> 00:31:17,767
I'll discreetly inquire.

621
00:31:18,408 --> 00:31:19,488
Might be Li Dongming.

622
00:31:20,367 --> 00:31:20,888
Okay.

623
00:31:22,127 --> 00:31:22,767
Hello, ma'am.

624
00:31:22,767 --> 00:31:23,688
What can I do for you?

625
00:31:24,448 --> 00:31:27,408
Is this
Ruijin Consulting's contracted hotel?

626
00:31:28,367 --> 00:31:31,888
Has a man, Mr. Li Dongming,
from that company checked in?

627
00:31:32,168 --> 00:31:34,208
He's my husband. I want to surprise him.

628
00:31:34,208 --> 00:31:35,607
So if he's staying here,

629
00:31:35,767 --> 00:31:36,728
I'd like a room too.

630
00:31:37,047 --> 00:31:37,847
Sorry, ma'am.

631
00:31:37,847 --> 00:31:39,688
We can't disclose guest information.

632
00:31:39,968 --> 00:31:42,047
Please contact your husband directly.

633
00:31:45,607 --> 00:31:47,168
What if I have his ID number?

634
00:31:47,928 --> 00:31:48,648
I'm sorry.

635
00:31:48,648 --> 00:31:49,728
I'm on a business trip.

636
00:31:50,127 --> 00:31:51,168
It's fine. Go ahead.

637
00:31:51,968 --> 00:31:53,367
Okay, sending it now.

638
00:31:57,488 --> 00:31:58,847
Qiao Hailun?

639
00:31:59,367 --> 00:32:00,888
(Qiao Hailun's WeChat Moments)
Nice name.

640
00:32:01,327 --> 00:32:02,527
She's quite pretty.

641
00:32:03,807 --> 00:32:05,327
But she has bad luck.

642
00:32:05,888 --> 00:32:07,327
Our company will have layoffs soon.

643
00:32:08,047 --> 00:32:09,527
She'll probably be laid off.

644
00:32:09,847 --> 00:32:10,367
Why?

645
00:32:11,327 --> 00:32:12,208
The worst performance?

646
00:32:12,767 --> 00:32:15,607
Because the company has its standards.

647
00:32:15,968 --> 00:32:18,688
Ma'am, is there anything else
I can help you with?

648
00:32:19,607 --> 00:32:21,968
Did he come with several colleagues?

649
00:32:23,087 --> 00:32:24,607
I can't tell you.

650
00:32:24,607 --> 00:32:25,168
I'm sorry.

651
00:32:28,087 --> 00:32:28,567
Thank you.

652
00:32:38,488 --> 00:32:39,767
Hello, Ruijin Consulting.

653
00:32:40,008 --> 00:32:40,968
How may I help you?

654
00:32:41,408 --> 00:32:42,127
Hello.

655
00:32:42,127 --> 00:32:44,648
Is Qiao Hailun not in the office today?

656
00:32:44,807 --> 00:32:46,287
I called her, but no one answered.

657
00:32:46,807 --> 00:32:47,928
Hold on, let me check.

658
00:32:50,968 --> 00:32:52,208
No, she's on a business trip.

659
00:32:53,688 --> 00:32:54,367
Okay, thank you.

660
00:32:54,847 --> 00:32:55,168
Goodbye.

661
00:33:01,888 --> 00:33:03,527
- Excuse me.
- Hello, ma'am.

662
00:33:03,527 --> 00:33:04,648
What can I do for you?

663
00:33:04,968 --> 00:33:06,888
Is there a car rental place here?

664
00:33:06,888 --> 00:33:09,127
Yes, there's one
right in front of the hotel.

665
00:33:09,127 --> 00:33:09,607
Thanks.

666
00:33:09,607 --> 00:33:10,367
You're welcome.

667
00:33:25,408 --> 00:33:25,928
I got this.

668
00:33:26,888 --> 00:33:27,527
Thank you.

669
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:05,760
(Li Dongming)

670
00:34:08,328 --> 00:34:09,328
I met with Barry.

671
00:34:10,408 --> 00:34:12,167
Although Barry didn't say much
outwardly,

672
00:34:12,768 --> 00:34:13,607
I know he understood.

673
00:34:13,607 --> 00:34:15,008
He took my words to heart.

674
00:34:16,328 --> 00:34:18,328
So he probably guessed
you were doing this for me?

675
00:34:19,207 --> 00:34:20,047
So what if he did?

676
00:34:20,647 --> 00:34:21,567
You're my wife.

677
00:34:21,567 --> 00:34:23,448
Fighting for you is only natural.

678
00:34:29,047 --> 00:34:30,087
From Barry's perspective,

679
00:34:31,527 --> 00:34:33,408
I was acting for your benefit and his.

680
00:34:34,808 --> 00:34:35,527
It's a win-win.

681
00:34:37,368 --> 00:34:38,488
My client is here.

682
00:34:39,968 --> 00:34:41,408
Let's talk in person tomorrow.

683
00:34:42,527 --> 00:34:42,968
Bye.

684
00:35:39,047 --> 00:35:41,488
Dong Yue, you're really no fun.

685
00:35:42,328 --> 00:35:43,607
I didn't ask you

686
00:35:43,607 --> 00:35:45,968
to have eight or ten beauties over.

687
00:35:46,008 --> 00:35:47,527
But you couldn't even have one?

688
00:35:47,928 --> 00:35:49,127
Can't I drink with you?

689
00:35:49,647 --> 00:35:50,888
Yes, you can,

690
00:35:50,888 --> 00:35:52,448
but it's not fun. We're two men.

691
00:35:52,448 --> 00:35:53,328
Not interested in you.

692
00:35:53,527 --> 00:35:54,607
Why did you ask me out?

693
00:35:54,727 --> 00:35:57,928
I thought you looked pitiful
traveling alone for work.

694
00:35:58,968 --> 00:36:00,888
It's a long night.

695
00:36:00,888 --> 00:36:02,167
And you're sleepless.

696
00:36:02,368 --> 00:36:05,527
I'm stopping you
from doing anything immoral.

697
00:36:05,808 --> 00:36:06,607
Fine, very good.

698
00:36:06,607 --> 00:36:08,527
Wait for me. Just a sec.

699
00:36:09,448 --> 00:36:10,768
Approaching a lady?

700
00:36:12,247 --> 00:36:13,008
Waiter!

701
00:36:13,008 --> 00:36:13,607
Yes, sir.

702
00:36:14,247 --> 00:36:15,087
What's going on?

703
00:36:15,368 --> 00:36:16,368
I didn't know

704
00:36:16,368 --> 00:36:17,488
you could drink that much.

705
00:36:21,448 --> 00:36:22,408
What are you doing here?

706
00:36:23,127 --> 00:36:24,328
I had a meeting in Hangzhou

707
00:36:24,607 --> 00:36:26,647
and came to Shanghai
to see some friends. And you?

708
00:36:28,408 --> 00:36:30,567
I... I'm here to get shots.

709
00:36:30,928 --> 00:36:31,448
Shots?

710
00:36:32,647 --> 00:36:33,488
Cosmetic injections.

711
00:36:34,368 --> 00:36:36,207
The doctors in Shanghai are better.

712
00:36:38,127 --> 00:36:39,567
Shouldn't you avoid alcohol then?

713
00:36:42,024 --> 00:36:42,952
Getting shots tomorrow.

714
00:36:43,527 --> 00:36:45,207
Drinking's fine today.

715
00:36:48,848 --> 00:36:49,567
Feeling down?

716
00:36:51,968 --> 00:36:53,288
I'm good.

717
00:36:55,328 --> 00:36:56,607
Want to join us?

718
00:36:57,328 --> 00:36:58,247
No socializing tonight.

719
00:36:58,567 --> 00:37:00,047
No, just meeting a friend of mine.

720
00:37:01,687 --> 00:37:03,727
What are you doing?

721
00:37:05,127 --> 00:37:06,848
Trying to play a good man?

722
00:37:07,328 --> 00:37:08,047
Exactly.

723
00:37:08,848 --> 00:37:10,127
You've drunk so much.

724
00:37:10,527 --> 00:37:11,328
Someone might

725
00:37:11,328 --> 00:37:12,207
take advantage of you.

726
00:37:12,207 --> 00:37:12,968
Too dangerous.

727
00:37:13,527 --> 00:37:14,288
Come on.

728
00:37:14,607 --> 00:37:15,527
Join us. Come on.

729
00:37:16,808 --> 00:37:17,328
Let's go.

730
00:37:18,448 --> 00:37:19,888
- Where are you sitting?
- Over there.

731
00:37:24,368 --> 00:37:24,808
Okay.

732
00:37:28,768 --> 00:37:31,768
I'll go to the restroom first.
Be right back.

733
00:37:32,207 --> 00:37:33,727
Okay, stop drinking.

734
00:37:37,328 --> 00:37:38,127
I help you up?

735
00:37:38,448 --> 00:37:39,288
No, I'm fine.

736
00:37:41,207 --> 00:37:41,848
Be right back.

737
00:37:44,368 --> 00:37:44,968
Are you okay?

738
00:37:46,888 --> 00:37:47,607
I'm good.

739
00:37:48,687 --> 00:37:49,607
I'll wait here for you.

740
00:37:52,607 --> 00:37:53,167
Right.

741
00:38:08,567 --> 00:38:09,527
I'm in Shanghai now.

742
00:38:09,808 --> 00:38:10,368
What?

743
00:38:11,328 --> 00:38:13,047
Why did you go there all of a sudden?

744
00:38:13,288 --> 00:38:14,328
We'll talk later.

745
00:38:15,448 --> 00:38:18,768
I just ran into Dong Yue
at the bar in this hotel.

746
00:38:19,527 --> 00:38:22,888
He said he went
to Hangzhou for a meeting this morning.

747
00:38:23,647 --> 00:38:24,647
But I think

748
00:38:24,647 --> 00:38:25,687
he lied to me.

749
00:38:26,167 --> 00:38:27,527
Help me find out

750
00:38:27,968 --> 00:38:30,527
if he really had a meeting
in Hangzhou this morning.

751
00:38:30,928 --> 00:38:31,808
Got it.

752
00:38:34,567 --> 00:38:36,207
There's something I forgot to tell you.

753
00:38:37,888 --> 00:38:39,928
Do you know
who Dong Yue's girlfriend is?

754
00:38:40,207 --> 00:38:40,768
Who?

755
00:38:42,448 --> 00:38:44,288
Shen Mo's daughter.

756
00:38:49,047 --> 00:38:50,207
Really?

757
00:38:53,047 --> 00:38:54,047
Interesting.

758
00:39:01,607 --> 00:39:04,888
So you're the knight
guarding the princess.

759
00:39:09,968 --> 00:39:11,087
You're quite interesting.

760
00:39:13,488 --> 00:39:15,087
Dong Yue, good for you.

761
00:39:15,127 --> 00:39:17,928
You picked up a pretty woman so fast.

762
00:39:19,047 --> 00:39:19,968
Hello there, beauty.

763
00:39:20,328 --> 00:39:21,207
May I have your name?

764
00:39:23,047 --> 00:39:23,567
Karen.

765
00:39:24,928 --> 00:39:25,488
Karen.

766
00:39:26,448 --> 00:39:27,448
Nice name.

767
00:39:29,368 --> 00:39:30,848
So you two...

768
00:39:31,567 --> 00:39:32,687
We're besties.

769
00:39:33,328 --> 00:39:34,087
Besties!

770
00:39:34,768 --> 00:39:36,647
You became best friends
in just a few minutes?

771
00:39:37,008 --> 00:39:38,047
That's great.

772
00:39:38,408 --> 00:39:42,408
Why did you come to the bar alone?

773
00:39:44,448 --> 00:39:46,368
I'm here on a business trip.

774
00:39:46,727 --> 00:39:49,288
I see. It's good to be alone.

775
00:39:49,288 --> 00:39:52,127
I prefer traveling alone for work,
feeling free.

776
00:39:52,647 --> 00:39:54,408
I can wander around everywhere,

777
00:39:54,408 --> 00:39:55,448
see the sights,

778
00:39:55,567 --> 00:39:57,928
meet new friends
while keeping the old ones.

779
00:39:57,928 --> 00:39:58,567
Right?

780
00:39:58,808 --> 00:40:01,488
Mr. Chen,
I guess you're good at singing.

781
00:40:01,808 --> 00:40:03,288
You guessed right.

782
00:40:03,288 --> 00:40:04,768
I'm actually good at singing.

783
00:40:05,527 --> 00:40:07,127
You seem to enjoy singing as well.

784
00:40:07,127 --> 00:40:08,448
Let's sing another day.

785
00:40:08,448 --> 00:40:09,888
Sure, let's do that.

786
00:40:10,768 --> 00:40:12,127
Should we order more drinks?

787
00:40:12,127 --> 00:40:13,368
There is not enough alcohol.

788
00:40:13,968 --> 00:40:16,368
Come on, order whatever you want.

789
00:40:16,567 --> 00:40:17,488
Go ahead.

790
00:40:19,727 --> 00:40:21,207
You've drunk a lot. Drink some water.

791
00:40:22,047 --> 00:40:23,488
Stay out of this.

792
00:40:23,968 --> 00:40:25,448
Mind your own business.

793
00:40:25,448 --> 00:40:27,527
Mind your own business, bestie.

794
00:40:27,527 --> 00:40:28,087
Exactly.

795
00:40:28,808 --> 00:40:31,087
Well, I think for girls,

796
00:40:31,448 --> 00:40:32,687
champagne is better.

797
00:40:33,368 --> 00:40:34,727
Champagne's good.

798
00:40:34,928 --> 00:40:35,288
Right.

799
00:40:35,647 --> 00:40:37,808
Champagne tastes like nothing,

800
00:40:38,087 --> 00:40:40,768
but it makes me drink easily.

801
00:40:40,848 --> 00:40:41,567
Once I get drunk,

802
00:40:41,567 --> 00:40:43,368
it'll be easier for you
to make a move on me.

803
00:40:44,488 --> 00:40:46,968
That's not what I meant!

804
00:40:47,848 --> 00:40:49,127
I was just joking with you.

805
00:40:50,047 --> 00:40:51,448
Don't take it seriously.

806
00:40:51,888 --> 00:40:52,647
You scared me.

807
00:40:52,647 --> 00:40:54,047
You're quite the joker.

808
00:40:54,488 --> 00:40:55,968
You're beautiful,

809
00:40:55,968 --> 00:40:57,047
and you have a nice voice.

810
00:40:57,448 --> 00:40:58,527
Everyone says so.

811
00:40:58,527 --> 00:40:59,328
Right?

812
00:41:00,448 --> 00:41:03,087
Dong Yue, you're the expert on drinks.

813
00:41:03,087 --> 00:41:04,448
Recommend something for her.

814
00:41:04,448 --> 00:41:05,488
No need.

815
00:41:05,607 --> 00:41:08,888
I'll have a bottle
of vintage Moonlight City.

816
00:41:09,008 --> 00:41:10,207
Just for the record,

817
00:41:10,207 --> 00:41:11,448
your bestie's paying today.

818
00:41:11,448 --> 00:41:14,288
Bestie, why are you being so stingy?

819
00:41:16,928 --> 00:41:17,607
Waitress!

820
00:41:17,928 --> 00:41:18,368
Coming.

821
00:41:20,888 --> 00:41:22,968
Two bottles of vintage Moonlight City.

822
00:41:23,448 --> 00:41:23,888
Okay.

823
00:41:25,288 --> 00:41:26,727
Mr. Dong, you're so generous.

824
00:41:27,368 --> 00:41:28,167
So generous indeed.

825
00:41:29,288 --> 00:41:29,888
Well,

826
00:41:30,288 --> 00:41:33,647
did you two know each other before?

827
00:41:33,647 --> 00:41:34,768
Looks like old friends.

828
00:41:35,464 --> 00:41:36,744
It's not an appointment, is it?

829
00:41:41,928 --> 00:41:44,047
If I'd made an appointment
with him beforehand,

830
00:41:44,047 --> 00:41:46,127
would I be here drinking with you?

831
00:41:47,968 --> 00:41:48,808
True.

832
00:41:49,448 --> 00:41:50,368
That makes sense.

833
00:41:50,647 --> 00:41:53,928
Bestie, where are you staying?

834
00:41:54,127 --> 00:41:55,527
I'm at the hotel next door.

835
00:41:55,527 --> 00:41:57,288
How about we grab late-night snacks?

836
00:41:57,647 --> 00:41:58,448
Cut it out.

837
00:41:58,448 --> 00:41:59,408
Get out of here.

838
00:41:59,408 --> 00:42:01,247
Being on a work trip alone is boring.

839
00:42:01,368 --> 00:42:02,527
It's a long,

840
00:42:02,527 --> 00:42:04,288
sleepless night.

841
00:42:04,288 --> 00:42:05,448
Tomorrow works too.

842
00:42:05,448 --> 00:42:07,167
How about we add each other on WeChat?

843
00:42:08,448 --> 00:42:09,328
Mr. Chen.

844
00:42:09,928 --> 00:42:11,087
No rush!

845
00:42:11,288 --> 00:42:12,567
Bonds are formed

846
00:42:12,567 --> 00:42:13,607
over drinks.

847
